$interpreted: Elio: The things we are doing...are we justified?
Angelia: What?
Elio: I mean obeying Sherlock and taking out those who threaten his position. Why would princess agree to help with such underhanded tactics?
Angelia: It's a mere exchange of interests. I don't think we did anything wrong.
Elio: You don't think what we're doing is shady?
Angelia: I will judge with my own values. Since you are my comrades, I hope that you can trust me.
Naya: Whew~ Angel, I did my investigation. Just as you predicted.
Naya: Turns out that bastard Sherlock didn't tell us the whole truth!
Elio: Princess, a mob is approaching. Could it be the group Sherlock mentioned?
Angelia: Hmm...there's the possibility of them uncovering my identity. I'll return to the Bazaar for some preparations.
Angelia: Naya, follow the plans. Take Elio with you and make contact with her.
Elio: Huh? What plan? How come I didn't know anything about it?
Naya: We'll talk while we move. Angel, please be careful on your own!
Karen: ...For beasts roaming the desert, your senses are awfully blunt.
Karen: You couldn't smell the difference in our power, or are you so hungry you've lost your minds──
Naya: ──No worries, we're here to save you!
Elio: Are you people alright?
Karen: One, I was never in danger.
Karen: Two, I'd never ask for help from you people.
Karen: However, as things have reached this point, I will still show my gratitude.
Naya: Tongue twister round-a-bout way of talking... You must be the president of the Commerce Chamber,
Naya: Karen Arla Fernandez, right?
Karen: One, from the way you ask, you knew who I am.
Karen: Two, from your reconfirmation, you approached me with a purpose.
Karen: Three. from the fact you have a purpose yet didn't tell me directly, you──
Elio: ──I-I believe she is indeed president Karen...
Naya: We are here on behalf of vice president Sherlock. He asked us to escort you back to the Bazaar to participate in the election.
Karen: By Sherlock, do you mean Sherlock Ortiz Agu──
Naya: ──Yes, yes, yes, that's the one. We better move quickly, or else we won't make the Commerce Chamber election in time.
Sherlock: Folks! The most important things for a merchant are goodwill and credibility! Even the president must follow the pre-determined voting time!
Spice Merchant: He has a point... not having credibility is the worst thing for a merchant.
Porcelain Merchant: Agreed. We can't wait any longer.
Sherlock: I hereby announce, those not present have automatically lost their right to vote. Everyone, please enter the venue!
Karen: ...Why is everybody still here!?
Sherlock: Wha, how...
Karen: One, not being seated in the venue at this time, will definitely result in the election being delayed.
Karen: Two, if delayed, it will affect future decisions as well.
Karen: Sherlock, you should've done a better job supervising everyone.
Sherlock: Yes... I understand...
Karen: Onward into the venue. As with the people you sent to escort me, have them wait outside.
Sherlock: Escort!?
Sherlock: Understood... all of you, wait here...
